$235935623_{74} = 2(74^8) + 3(74^7) + 5(74^6) + 9(74^5) + 3(74^4) + 5(74^3) + 6(74^2) + 2(74^1) + 3(74^0)$
Since $74 = 2 \times 37$, $235935623_{74}$ is an integer.
$235935623_{74} \equiv 235935623 \pmod{15}$.
We need to find the remainder of $235935623$ when divided by $15$.
$235935623 \div 15$
$235935623 = 15 \times 15729041 + 8$.
Thus, $235935623 \equiv 8 \pmod{15}$.
We have $235935623_{74} \equiv 8 \pmod{15}$.
We want $235935623_{74} - a \equiv 0 \pmod{15}$.
$8-a \equiv 0 \pmod{15}$
$8-a = 15k$ for some integer $k$.
$8-a = 15k$.
$8-a = 0, 15, 30, \dots$ or $8-a = -15, -30, \dots$.
Since $0 \le a \le 14$, we have $8 - a = 0$.
$8 - a = 0 \implies a = 8$.
Also, $8 - a = -15$ gives $a = 23$, which is not possible since $0 \le a \le 14$.
Thus, $a = 8$.
